en_2850837_0	Promotional activities of the Surya Bala Sangramaya project aimed at encouraging the use of solar energy in households commenced on Friday.
en_2850837_1	One million houses will be introduced to solar energy under this programme.
en_2850837_2	The project is a joint venture of the Ministry of Power and Renewable Energy , The Ceylon Electricity Board , Sri Lanka Sustainable Energy Authority and several other organisation.
en_2850837_3	The commencement took place from Trincomalee, Ampara, Jaffna and Hambantota on Friday morning.
en_2850837_4	After the motorcades reach Colombo, the inauguration of this national project will take place at the BMICH on September 6 under the auspices of President Maithripala Sirisena.
